OL,3,CMother, 28, jailed for violently
OL,4,Cshaking her baby to death
OL,6,F"Lexi was killed by you when the
OL,7,Fcountry was in the first national
OL,8,FCovid-19 lockdown.
OL,10,F"After the evening meal you were
OL,11,Fbathing Lexi and you shook Lexi, and
OL,12,Fimmediately after this she went floppy.
OL,14,F"Your shaking of Lexi led to severe
OL,15,Fbleeding in her brain. I am sure on
OL,16,Fthe evidence that Lexi had been shaken
OL,17,Fby you in another, less violent,
OL,18,Fincident before that Easter Sunday.
OL,19,FOnly you will know why you acted in
OL,20,Fthe way you did.
