OL,6,F"On the morning of 18 April, Lexi
OL,7,Fseemed to have longer pauses in her
OL,8,Fbreathing. Ms Wilband was told to
OL,9,Fattend the ward.
OL,11,F"She arrived just after Lexi had
OL,12,Fceased to show any signs of life and
OL,13,Fhad stopped breathing."
OL,15,FA post-mortem examination gave Lexi's
OL,16,Fcause of death as bleeding to the
OL,17,Fbrain, caused by a non-accidental
OL,18,Ftraumatic event such as someone
OL,19,F"shaking her violently", Ms Osborne
OL,20,Fsaid.
